FBIS4-32966 "drlat105_b_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Invasion Rumors Generate Fear, Concern Invasion Rumors Generate Fear, Concern FL3105201394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1300 GMT 31 May 94 FL3105201394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] On the night of 30 May, rumors of military intervention exacerbated fear and worry among Haitian families; rumors that the U.S. military was controlling Mais Gate Airport. The rumors appear to have stemmed from a U.S. officer's statement on the military invasion of Haiti that was misunderstood. A reliable source told Signal FM that a U.S. Army colonel said U.S. authorities have decided to invade Haiti and that all that remains now is to determine the main targets. This Army colonel also said Mais Gate Airport will be one of the main targets.
